Karana server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 819<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/01 11:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yooohoo the hope reborn</span><hr size=1> You know, that whole &quot;6 Wizards on a rampage&quot; is such a crock of reasty dung its difficult to overstate.  If that was possible then 6 Wizards would run around NOW and kill things, you ever SEE an all Wizard group?  Seriously?  Put aside that there are not that many Wizards on any server, and think about it.  We all know what happens when we cast spells on creatures.<br>
<br>
With no tanks to protect, no healers to keep us alive, no enchanter/mage/shaman etc to lower resistances and give mana back, the group would suffer horrible losses, kill once every 10 minutes or so, and have virutally no effect on the game.  In fact, it would be so poor a strategy that its not even worth considering.<br>
<br>
DOUBLE Wizard's power and this doesn't change, not even a little.  Verant is such a batch or morons when it comes to Wizards, I can't even imagine what the hell happened to them as children. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufastasia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fastasia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Saintly Sorceress</font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/01 3:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yooohoo the hope reborn</span><hr size=1> If they do not address the mana issue in some fashion, we will not be fixed on large hp mobs. End of story in my opinion. A rogue can do 76 points of damage per second unlimited except for the cleric mana. That is 45,600 points of damage over a 10 minute fight (many last much longer)<br>
<br>
A wiz cannot nuke then med then nuke again because we have to wait for aggro to build and then even then, sitting to med is a dicey proposition. Even at level 60 with massive mana gear and Dragon or Giants bane, you will only do about 14,000 points of damage in a 10 minute fight. That is less than a third the damage ONE rogue can do. Lets say for sake of argument that you can nuke out, med to full and nuke out again in 10 minutes (is not possible with current aggro rules) you would still only do 28,000 which is barely over half what a rogue will do.<br>
<br>
They have to address the mana issue. If they say it is a non issue, then they are not properly considering the problems. The two new spells are NOT a fix. Currently NO ONE has the dragonsbane spells, and few of us have bothered to get the giants bane. I can currently use Giants bane on Tormax (yeah right) and Velketor. Even if these spells did 5000 damage for the same amount they would still put you behind rogues....<br>
<br>
just some thoughts.<br>
<br>
Fasty <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 7:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Echo, echo, echo...</span><hr size=1> This is all math that many of us have calculated for months and months now.  The overall damage output problem is obvious.  We already know they are not looking properly at the situation.  I venture to say that they aren't really looking at the situation AT ALL.  Even REMOTELY suggesting that they made a mistake yields the childs temper tantrum response.  (i.e. Hold breath and fold arms until the bad people go away)<br>
